body:
I use cmake to build mxnet with cuda 7.0 and visual studio 2013. I got the error:

nvcc error : 'ptxas' died with status 0xC0000005

@happynear , did you get the same error message?

@ommiissyu 
I haven't seen this in mxnet. But I got this error when I was configuring cxxnet. 
Add `-Xptxas -O1` to `CUDA C/C++ -> Command Line`, can solve this problem.

@hjk41,
You can download mingw64 dlls form http://sourceforge.net/projects/openblas/files/v0.2.14/ . It is at the bottom of the list.
I will add them to the `mxnet_thirdparty.zip`, too.

@hjk41 We do not want to pack a binary lib file, mainly for License issues. I

For now, we are fine with a windows binary dll file, and have a script(or provide instruction) to help user to download the other dependent dll from their official site.

All the python and R binary distribution can dependent on this one. We do not need to distribute binary for now on linux
